    "name": "Graphite",
    "description": "Graphite is proposed as an algorithmic framework for unsupervised learning of representations over nodes in large graphs using deep latent variable generative models. Technically, the model parameterizes variational autoencoders (VAEs) with graph neural networks and incorporates a novel iterative graph refinement strategy inspired by low-rank approximations during decoding. Graphite demonstrated superior performance compared to competing approaches on various synthetic and benchmark datasets for tasks such as density estimation, link prediction, and node classification. Additionally, the work theoretically connects message passing in graph neural networks to mean-field variational inference.",
